--[[
    FEATURES
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    ☰  MENU         – FPS counter, Shift-Lock, Low Graphics, Hide Players,
                      Nameplates, Reset Character, Rejoin, Leave, …

    💬  SERVER CHAT  – Echoes your messages locally. When OTHER players on
                       the same server also run this script, their messages
                       appear too (via a shared RemoteEvent auto-created at
                       runtime — no pre-placed ServerScript required, but a
                       server-side relay IS needed for cross-client delivery;
                       see note at bottom).

    🌐  GLOBAL CHAT  – Cross-server chat via MessagingService.
                       Requires a published game (not Studio solo-test).

    🔔  NOTIFICATIONS – Slide-in toasts bottom-right.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    Everything is in this ONE file.
    NOTE: Roblox's security model means a LocalScript alone cannot relay
    messages to OTHER clients. For full cross-player Server Chat, paste the
    small relay block below into a Script in ServerScriptService:

        local RS = game:GetService("ReplicatedStorage")
        local folder = RS:WaitForChild("CGUIv1",10)
        if not folder then return end
        local re = folder:WaitForChild("LocalChat",10)
        if not re then return end
        re.OnServerEvent:Connect(function(player, msg)
            if type(msg)~="string" then return end
            msg = msg:sub(1,200)
            for _, p in ipairs(game:GetService("Players"):GetPlayers()) do
                re:FireClient(p, player.Name, msg)
            end
        end)

    Without that relay, Server Chat works as a local echo only (you see
    your own messages; Global Chat still works cross-server normally).
]]

